    {
      "id": "FGlQT0rLd5lHPLw2yAVo-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3497.9420866694354,
      "y": -354.6211483958073,
      "width": 2604.1627963704823,
      "height": 300.7143207150852,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "7fwSgrbkN7GhfPmv4rlvY",
        "lm6tMU2n8Y3f6kvzoQwbQ"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0NV",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1841292213,
      "version": 1108,
      "versionNonce": 496103387,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1766015297808,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Some incentive not to stay there too long (preferably fun)\n- Night time mobs are overwhelming and force you into the hole\n- Mostly barren but you could probably set some things up to make recurring trips more fun. Deciding on if to reward the player for making it back up, or if they should just die. (item recovery like minecraft, or subsequent trips like terraria hellevator)\n- The whole point of the game is that each trip down the hole you are more prepared than the last, so perhaps you can set up infrastructure on the surface to process minerals or store items\n- Will most likely be isolated like minecraft\n- If we are going with Alien planet, then perhaps at night the surface becomes completely engulfed in flame or some other natural phenomenon (think rain world)\n- The only thing is that we need to make sure it is a fun loop and not an annoyance. the player shouldnt have toooo much to do on the surface and should ALWAYS be incentivized to do long runs in the cave. (no waiting out the night, or little quick trips for items)\n\nI want it to be beautiful\n- Grass and flower and maybe a few trees. beautiful sun beams. almost surreal\n- not too much elevation change. rolling hills at most\n- some incentive to stay near the hole. maybe traveling too far teleports you back, or better yet it could loop around like White Space. or some creature or deity that is afraid of the hole murders you lmao",
      "fontSize": 20.047621381005676,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Some incentive not to stay there too long (preferably fun)\n- Night time mobs are overwhelming and force you into the hole\n- Mostly barren but you could probably set some things up to make recurring trips more fun. Deciding on if to reward the player for making it back up, or if they should just die. (item recovery like minecraft, or subsequent trips like terraria hellevator)\n- The whole point of the game is that each trip down the hole you are more prepared than the last, so perhaps you can set up infrastructure on the surface to process minerals or store items\n- Will most likely be isolated like minecraft\n- If we are going with Alien planet, then perhaps at night the surface becomes completely engulfed in flame or some other natural phenomenon (think rain world)\n- The only thing is that we need to make sure it is a fun loop and not an annoyance. the player shouldnt have toooo much to do on the surface and should ALWAYS be incentivized to do long runs in the cave. (no waiting out the night, or little quick trips for items)\n\nI want it to be beautiful\n- Grass and flower and maybe a few trees. beautiful sun beams. almost surreal\n- not too much elevation change. rolling hills at most\n- some incentive to stay near the hole. maybe traveling too far teleports you back, or better yet it could loop around like White Space. or some creature or deity that is afraid of the hole murders you lmao",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
